        <head xml:id="la30px-aaa367-Hd1e104">Proposition 5</head>
        <p xml:id="la30px-aaa367-d1e106">
          Proposition 5
        </p>
        <p xml:id="la30px-aaa367-d1e111">
          The Supreme Pontiff, by his authority in the earth from Jesus Christ, can obligate Christian princes and kings to go on expeditions to achieve this Christian end, at their own expenses, by their royal persons, or by ideal ministers. He can do this if he sees it necessary or very expedient to achieve or not impede this said end. By this same authority he can also impose taxes on all Christendom.
        </p>
